. cat  command is used to show the content of a files and also to combine several files together in one file.
. The cat command does not accept directories as input.

Syntax:
    cat options <filename>


==> View content of file
    cat list1.txt

==> View content of multiple files
    cat list1.txt list2.txt

==> View content of file alongwith line number
    cat -b list1.txt
    Note: This won't add line number on blank line

    cat -n list1.txt
    Note: This will add line number on blank line as well

    cat -s list1.txt
    Note: It squeezes multiple blank line into one

    cat -E list1.txt
    Note: It adds $ to end of the line
    


